To say that 2020 has been a testing year is an understatement. The coronavirus pandemic has wreaked havoc all over the place. As of the time of writing, the virus had infected about 80 million and killed 1.75 million people globally. In Kenya, the official count stood at 95,843 infections and 1,655 deaths.



