The country’s sorry public health system, spared a catastrophic overrun only by the relatively low infection rates in our part of the world, is ending the year even much weaker, with a majority of workers in government hospitals on strike.
 The Education Cabinet Secretary once declared 2020 a lost year before announcing a phased reopening. For all its uncertainties, the year of the pandemic also confirmed or reinforced some widely held views of the country.
Kenya is a politicking nation
Coronavirus? What coronavirus? Large social gatherings have been identified worldwide as potential super-spreader events for the virus. But in Kenya, a ban on political rallies as part of the initial public health guidelines introduced to try to contain the spread of the virus was honoured more in the breach than the observance.



